      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Absolutely, you should definitely try to negotiate the wording, as this clause is often one of the most heavily weighted in a contract. You can try to limit your indemnification only to claims arising directly from your *negligence* or *willful misconduct*, rather than *any* third-party claim. Asking for a mutual indemnity clause where they also cover claims related to their own provided materials is also a common balancing tactic.",
